{"word":"ὑλάω","slug":"ὑλάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑλάω</b></el> <el>(ὑ˘λάω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to howl, bark, bay</i>, of dogs, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>κύνες οὐχ ὑλάοντο</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to bark</i> or <i>bay at</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>Formed from the sound.\n"}]}